i18n.modal.engraving.content:
The engraving completes your wedding rings, making them unique, that you should remember the most beautiful day of your life forever. We offer the following two methods with which the rings can be engraved.

Diamond engraving

With classic diamond engraving, the selected text is transferred to the inside of the ring using a fine diamond stylus and the engraving is precisely carved into the inside of the ring.

Laser engraving

A precise laser beam burns the material selectively, creating a deep and easy-to-read engraving on the inside.
i18n.tab.engraving.heading: engraving
i18n.modal.diamonds.content:
Stone trim

We only use diamonds from well-known German stone suppliers to ensure that no blood diamonds are used. A diamond becomes a brilliant through its cut. Diamonds are available in a wide variety of shapes. The classic is the diamond, which gets its characteristic fire from the round cut with 57 facets. The quality of the diamonds is expressed by the 4 C:

Carat (carat, weight), Color (color), Clarity (purity) and Cut (cut)

Barrel types

Rubbed in

This version is the most popular type of barrel. The stone is worked into the material of the ring and is therefore well protected. The stone is inserted into a conical recess and the surrounding metal is pressed / driven over the stone.

Waste

This type of setting has only established itself in wedding rings in the last few years. Only held by small grains, the diamonds sit next to each other and look extremely lively. Nevertheless, the stones sit securely in this type of barrel and will last a lifetime.

channel

With the channel setting, a kind of channel is laid on the surface of the ring, in which the stones are attached. The diamonds are held laterally in the material of the ring.

Tension ring look

Here the diamond is "clamped" in the ring band. The stone is held in the ring rail by means of the pressure / tension force on both sides. The diamond gives the impression that it is floating in the ring band.
i18n.tab.diamonds.heading: Stone setting / barrel types
i18n.modal.groove.content: Design joints and steps give the already individually designed wedding ring a different look. The steps on the edge of the wedding ring set the accents and the design joints in the middle part create the wedding ring according to your own ideas.

i18n.modal.metals.content:
Alloys are the proportions of the precious metals.

All of our alloys are nickel free.

Alloys are created by mixing several metals. The precious metals gold, silver and platinum cannot be processed in their pure state. Only when other metals are added does the wedding ring alloy acquire the properties necessary for further processing.

For example, gold is the classic among materials and is also the most diverse. The higher the proportion of gold in the overall alloy, the softer the material and the richer the color.

You can customize the design of your rings to suit your personal taste. Different surfaces, precious metals and colors are available and make "your" ring unique.
i18n.tab.metals.heading: Precious metal
i18n.modal.dimensions.content:
Here you select the width and height of the ring band, as well as the desired ring size.

When determining the ring size, we at JC Wedding Rings are the right contact for you.

Please note that larger stones can be set in higher and wider ring bands and the engravings are particularly effective.
i18n.tab.dimensions.heading: Ring gauges
i18n.modal.profiles.content:
There are many different types of ring profiles, a distinction is made between cambered and non-cambered rings. The arched inner and / or outer shape of rings is called crowning.

The ring can be easily pushed over the joints and fits snugly against the finger. The more pronounced the camber, the greater the wearing comfort.

Profiles 00, 01, 08, 12, 13 are ideally suited for side stones.
